author: RAMENDRA SINGH
description: Pragya Jaiswal, a 16-year-old from Singrauli, MP, achieved a perfect score in her Class 10 state board exams, a remarkable feat in a district with low female literacy. Her success has inspired her village to prioritize girls' education and seek government support for a girls' school. Supported by her teacher parents, Pragya aims to become an IAS officer and is now seeking better educational opportunities for her Class 12 studies.
title: Girl in district with 49% female literacy gets 100% in Boards

author: TNN
description: Foreign Minister Jaishankar highlighted the significance of skill development and international mobility in enhancing India's global influence, emphasizing the need for legal pathways and combating illegal migration. The government is reassessing the Emigration Act 1983 to align with current realities and promote opportunities while safeguarding vulnerable individuals. He also acknowledged the increasing expectations of Indian citizens abroad for government support, especially in challenging situations.
title: Government reviewing Act that regulates mobility: EAM S Jaishankar

author: TNN
description: After three years of negotiations, India and the UK have finalized a trade agreement that eliminates tariffs on 99% of Indian exports and reduces duties on 90% of tariff lines. The deal includes exemptions from social security contributions for Indian workers on temporary visas, potentially saving them around 20% of their salary. PM Modi highlighted the agreement's potential to boost trade, investment, and job creation in both economies.
title: Government seals trade pact with UK: Tariffs cut, savings for Indians on work visas

author: AMBIKA PANDIT
description: India's Human Development Index ranking improved to 130th in 2023, driven by increased life expectancy and progress in education and income. The nation's HDI value has risen significantly since 1990, outpacing global and South Asian averages, fueled by economic growth and social programs. However, inequality continues to significantly reduce India's HDI, with income and gender disparities remaining a challenge.
title: Income and gender disparities in India still significant, says UNDP

author: AMBIKA PANDIT
description: The 2025 Human Development Report recognises India as a burgeoning "AI powerhouse," showcasing significant AI skills penetration and improved talent retention. Notably, 20% of Indian AI researchers now stay in the country, a stark contrast to 2019. The report emphasises AI's potential to revitalise development, with surveys indicating widespread optimism about its impact on productivity and job creation.
title: India a rising AI powerhouse, talent retention growing: Report

author: SAGAR KUMAR MUTHA
description: A special CBI court in Hyderabad convicted Gali Janardhan Reddy and three others in the Obulapuram Mining Company illegal mining case, sentencing them to seven years imprisonment after a 13-year trial. BRS MLA Sabitha Indra Reddy and ex-industries secretary B Kripanandam were acquitted due to lack of evidence.
title: Karnataka mining baron-MLA held guilty in Obulapuram case

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Following India's 'Operation Sindoor' against terror camps in Pakistan-occupied Kashmir after the Pahalgam attack, IndiGo Airlines reports flight disruptions. Airspace changes over northern India are causing delays and cancellations for flights to and from Srinagar, Jammu, Amritsar, Leh, Chandigarh, Dharamshala, and Bikaner. Indian air defence units along the border are on high alert amid heightened tensions.
title: Operation Sindoor: Flight service impacted in Northern India

author: RICHA PINTO
description: Mumbai's municipal corporation is set for elections after three years under state-appointed administration, a period marked by significant infrastructure projects like road repairs costing ₹12,000 crore and rising liabilities. Former corporators lament the lack of accountability and neglect of local issues, while preparations for the upcoming polls are underway, with parties aiming to increase their representation and address citizen grievances.
title: Over 3-year-gap the longest BMC has gone without elected body

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Indian Armed Forces launched 'Operation Sindoor,' targeting nine sites in Pakistan and Pakistan-occupied Jammu and Kashmir, focusing on terrorist infrastructure of Jaish-e-Mohammed and Lashkar-e-Taiba, including their headquarters in Bahawalpur and Muridke. The strikes, a response to the Pahalgam terror attack, were precise and non-escalatory, specifically avoiding Pakistani military facilities.

title: 'Bharat Mata ki Jai': Rajnath Singh hails 'Operation Sindoor'

author: DHANANJAY.MAHAPATRA
description: The Supreme Court has directed the Maharashtra State Election Commission to conduct local body elections within four weeks, disapproving of bureaucratic control due to election delays. The elections will proceed based on OBC reservation specifications as they existed before the Banthia Commission's report in July 2022, addressing concerns about the enumeration of the OBC population and ensuring grassroots democracy.

description: In response to the deadly Pahalgam attack that killed 26, India launched "Operation Sindoor," targeting nine terrorist camps in Pakistan and Pakistan-occupied Kashmir. The strikes were described as precise, measured, and non-escalatory, with no Pakistani military facilities targeted. This action follows Prime Minister Modi granting the armed forces full operational freedom.

author: TOI NEWS DESK

A detailed briefing is scheduled, with the Indian Army declaring, "Justice is served."

author: TNN
description: Unseasonal rain, thunderstorms, and strong winds have tragically resulted in 17 deaths across Gujarat in the past 24 hours. The severe weather, impacting 168 talukas, caused fatalities due to lightning, electrocution, and structural collapses. Amreli and Bhavnagar experienced heavy rainfall and fierce winds, providing relief from the heat but causing significant damage to crops like mango, onion, sesame, and bajra.
title: 17 killed in rain-related mishaps across Gujarat, several injured

author: SUBRATA CHATTORAJ
description: Calcutta High Court expressed concern over lawyers' political alignment and declining court decorum during a hearing on alleged police overreach in the Murshidabad violence case. Justice Tirthankar Ghosh observed that lawyers' power seems to stem from outside the courtroom, leading to heated exchanges. He refused to entertain the plea, directing it to a division bench already addressing Murshidabad violence-related cases.
title: Calcutta high court: Lawyers now aligned with political parties

author: TNN
description: The Delhi High Court has temporarily suspended a copyright order against AR Rahman and the creators of 'Ponniyin Selvan 2' concerning a song dispute. While staying the single judge's order to credit the Dagar brothers and deposit ₹2 crore, the court instructed Rahman and the filmmakers to deposit the said amount with the HC registry within 10 days. The matter is scheduled for further review on May 23.
title: Delhi HC stays order against AR Rahman in copyright row

author: DEBABRATA MOHAPATRA
description: Odisha Chief Minister Mohan Charan Majhi has formally requested West Bengal Chief Minister Mamata Banerjee to cease using the term 'Jagannath Dham' for the Digha temple, asserting that it exclusively pertains to Puri. This appeal follows widespread objections and concerns that the usage dilutes Puri's unique religious and cultural significance, potentially hurting the sentiments of numerous pilgrims and misrepresenting the revered abode of Lord Jagannath.
title: Drop ‘Jagannath Dham’ from Digha temple name, Odisha CM urges Mamata

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: In a thrilling, rain-interrupted match at Wankhede, the Gujarat Titans clinched a nail-biting three-wicket victory against the Mumbai Indians on the very last ball. Chasing 156, Shubman Gill's 43 and crucial contributions down the order guided the Titans to the top of the league standings.
title: Gujarat Titans snatch thrilling last-ball win over Mumbai Indians in a rain-hit thriller

author: TAPAN SUSHEEL
description: In a historic move, IIT Roorkee has dismissed Professor Zillur Rahman from his position in the department of management studies after a PhD student filed a sexual harassment complaint against him. Following an internal inquiry and opportunities for Rahman to present his case, the Board of Governors approved his dismissal. This marks the first instance of such action in the institute's history.
title: IIT-Roorkee professor axed for sex harassment

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Gujarat Titans surged to the top of the IPL 2025 points table after defeating Mumbai Indians, securing their eighth win. Royal Challengers Bengaluru and Punjab Kings closely follow, intensifying the playoff race. Delhi Capitals remain in contention, while Sunrisers Hyderabad were eliminated. Rajasthan Royals and Chennai Super Kings have bowed out of playoff contention, making every remaining match crucial.
title: IPL 2025 Points Table: Latest standings after GT vs MI match

author: PRAFULLA MARPAKWAR
description: Following the Supreme Court's clearance for civic elections in Maharashtra, Chief Minister Devendra Fadnavis announced that the Mahayuti alliance, comprising BJP, Shiv Sena, and NCP, will contest as a unified entity. However, uncertainty looms over the MVA alliance, consisting of Congress, Shiv Sena (UBT), and NCP (SP), regarding their united participation in the upcoming polls.
title: Mahayuti to fight civic polls unitedly, MVA non-committal

author: GAUREE MALKARNEKAR
description: The Goa Coastal Zone Management Authority (GCZMA) is considering a proposal to allow event organizers to obtain a three-year permit for hosting up to 40 weddings on specific beach stretches for a fee of Rs 7 lakh. The GCZMA has also proposed changes to application fees for various construction projects, including hotels, swimming pools, and infrastructure for petroleum products, while introducing fees for flood protection walls and coastal structures.
title: New proposal: Pay Rs 7L, have 40 beach weddings in 3 years

author: DIPAK K DASH
description: The government has notified a scheme for free cashless treatment to road accident victims nationwide, complying with a Supreme Court deadline. Up to ₹1.5 lakh will be provided for treatment for a maximum of seven days at 30,000 designated hospitals. A steering committee will monitor the scheme's implementation, with ₹272 crore allocated for 2025-26.
title: Road crash victims will now get free, cashless treatment

author: DIPAK K DASH
description: The Supreme Court has instructed the road transport ministry to release the "Road Accidents in India 2023" report by August, emphasizing the need for timely publication within six months of each calendar year's end for its utility. Concerns are raised by road safety experts regarding delays in publishing crucial accident data, hindering effective interventions. The National Crime Records Bureau is also yet to release its 2023 report.
title: Supreme Court to Centre: Publish road accidents report 2023 by August

author: TNN
description: A BJP functionary, B Saranya, was murdered and beheaded near Thanjavur, with her stepson and two others surrendering in Madurai, confessing to the crime. Police investigation revealed that the murder stemmed from a domestic dispute over property, not political motivations, despite her prior arrest for protesting against a minister. The incident has sparked outrage, with BJP leaders criticizing the state government over rising crime rates against women.
title: Woman BJP cadre beheaded by armed gang in Thanjavur

author: NASEER GANAI
description: In a tragic incident near the Line of Control in Kupwara, an Army vehicle accident resulted in the death of two soldiers and injuries to two others. The vehicle plunged into a deep gorge after the driver lost control. This unfortunate event follows a similar accident in Ramban just two days prior, where three Army personnel lost their lives.
title: Army duo dead, 3 injured in Kupwara road accident

author: SANJAY KHAJURIA
description: A passenger bus accident in Jammu and Kashmir's Poonch district resulted in the tragic loss of four lives, including an Army soldier on leave, and left over 40 individuals injured. The bus, en route from Ghani to Mendhar, veered off course and plunged into a deep gorge, prompting immediate rescue efforts by locals, police, Army, and CRPF personnel.
title: Four dead as bus falls into Poonch gorge

author: OMER FAROOQ KHAN
description: Iranian Foreign Minister Abbas Araghchi's recent diplomatic efforts in Islamabad, including meetings with Pakistani leaders, centered on mediating the escalating tensions between India and Pakistan following the Pahalgam terrorist attack. Despite India's reluctance to accept third-party mediation, Iran is positioning itself as a regional conciliator, leveraging its ties with both nations to push for de-escalation.

author: NASEER GANAI
description: Following the Pahalgam attack, Omar Abdullah and Mehbooba Mufti voiced concerns over large-scale detentions in J&K, fearing a message of collective punishment. Mehbooba highlighted that thousands of civilians have been taken into custody, with over 3,000 arrests and nearly 100 PSA detentions reported, urging a review of this approach to avoid deepening the trust deficit.

author: SRINIVAS LAXMAN
description: The US Congressional Budget Office projects that the cost of operating, sustaining, and modernizing US nuclear forces will surge to $946 billion between 2025 and 2034, a 25% increase from the previous estimate. This substantial investment includes modernizing delivery systems, weapons, facilities, and command and control systems. The rise is attributed to the need to replace aging legacy weapon systems and address cost overruns in programs like the Sentinel ICBM.

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Mallikarjun Kharge alleged PM Modi cancelled his Kashmir visit after an intelligence report warned of an attack and questioned why security wasn't reinforced for civilians if there was intelligent inputs. The BJP strongly condemned Kharge's remarks, accusing him of echoing Pakistan's narrative and demanding an apology.

description: Microsoft is implementing a two-year rehire ban for underperforming employees and tracking "good attrition," signaling a stricter management approach. This policy shift, revealed in internal documents, mirrors similar practices at other tech giants like Amazon and Meta. description: West Bengal CM Mamata Banerjee accused external elements of instigating violence in the state, urging people to resist divisive agendas promoted by the BJP and religious fundamentalists. Speaking in Murshidabad, she asserted that the Waqf Act would not be implemented in Bengal, appealing for calm amidst potential protests.

description: The Trump administration has barred Harvard University from receiving new federal research grants, escalating a dispute over antisemitism, academic standards, and campus management. Education Secretary Linda McMahon accused Harvard of violating legal duties, citing concerns over protests, foreign student admissions, and DEI initiatives. Harvard has responded with a lawsuit, alleging government overreach and infringement of First Amendment rights.
title: Trump blocks Harvard's billion-dollar funding, demands sweeping overhaul

description: Sean "Diddy" Combs' federal trial is underway, marked by sex trafficking, rape, and coercion charges stemming from numerous civil lawsuits alleging decades of abuse. A 2016 video showing Combs assaulting Cassie Ventura has surfaced, potentially influencing jury selection. With Combs pleading not guilty, the trial promises to be a high-profile legal battle.
title: Sean 'Diddy' Combs trial: CCTV footage of rapper assaulting Cassie becomes focus

description: In a surprising turn, ChatGPT creator OpenAI will remain under nonprofit control, reversing plans for a for-profit transition. This decision follows internal debates, scrutiny from Microsoft and Elon Musk, and concerns raised by authorities. Microsoft, a major investor, reportedly sought greater control, while Musk sued OpenAI, alleging abandonment of its original mission.
title: Surprise and Shock as ChatGPT maker takes HUGE U-Turn: It is Elon Musk or ...

description: Amidst US tariff hike proposals in April, Indian investors demonstrated savvy investment strategies by increasing their investments in overseas equities, particularly in the US. Platforms like INDMoney and HDFC Securities reported significant surges in investment activity, with a notable rise in new investors targeting US stocks. This enthusiasm was fueled by the perception of market volatility as a buying opportunity, especially in sectors like AI and tech.
title: Indians rush to buy the dip on Wall Street amid market chaos

description: Moody's Rating warns that escalating tensions with India could negatively impact Pakistan's growth, fiscal stability, and macroeconomic situation. Pakistan's weak fundamentals and reliance on IMF bailouts make it vulnerable. While Pakistan's economy shows signs of improvement, persistent tensions could strain its foreign exchange reserves and access to external financing. In contrast, India's economy is expected to remain stable, with minimal disruption due to limited economic ties with Pakistan.
title: Prolonged tension to hurt Pakistan's economy: Moody's

description: The United Nations Security Council convened closed-door consultations on Monday to address the escalating tensions between India and Pakistan, following a request from Pakistan. Secretary-General António Guterres expressed deep concern over the deteriorating relations, particularly after the deadly terror attack in Pahalgam, Jammu and Kashmir, which resulted in the loss of 26 civilian lives.
title: UNSC holds closed-door consultations amid escalating India-Pakistan tensions

description: During an RCB vs CSK match in Bengaluru, a heated dispute erupted in the Diamond Box between the families of a senior IPS officer and an income tax commissioner over seating arrangements. The argument escalated, leading to allegations of intimidation, sexual harassment, and outraging modesty.
title: Families of IPS, I-T officers clash over seat at Diamond Box during RCB match
